Causes of Death in the United States 1999-2020

Causes of Death:

    Total Deaths from 1999-2020

    • Like with our state data, we see a clear uptick in deaths in 2020
      • This is likely caused by the COVID-19 Pandemic
    • Year to year fluctuations in deaths are very muted on a national level
      • At a national level, the upticks and downticks in various causes of death mean the totals even out over 50 states and Washington D.C..
    • The United States has consistently seen population growth over its history. Thus, we see an increasing number of deaths each year. More people understandably means more deaths.
